D i s t r i b u t i o n: 
<collectingCountry id="46D7761EFFEA472AFE387A16FDB8FE92" box="[417,560,323,345]" name="Turkmenistan" pageId="12" pageNumber="941">Turkmenistan</collectingCountry>
, south-eastern 
<collectingCountry id="46D7761EFFEA472AFD517A16FC9DFE92" box="[712,789,323,345]" name="Turkey" pageId="12" pageNumber="941">Turkey</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3E7F368EFFEA472AFF2B7A3CFEB3FE38" blockId="12.[178,1087,360,499]" pageId="12" pageNumber="941">
R e m a r k s: the authors regard this as a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName id="F9C04D0DFFEA472AFC897A3DFC41FEB5" baseAuthorityName="STAUDINGER" baseAuthorityYear="1891" box="[784,969,360,382]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Bembecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="941" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pontica">
<emphasis id="0CB4EA9CFFEA472AFC897A3DFC41FEB5" box="[784,969,360,382]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="941">Bembecia pontica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and not of 
<taxonomicName id="F9C04D0DFFEA472AFF2B7AD0FE3EFE50" baseAuthorityName="STAUDINGER" baseAuthorityYear="1891" box="[178,438,389,411]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Bembecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="941" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="transcaucasica">
<emphasis id="0CB4EA9CFFEA472AFF2B7AD0FE3EFE50" box="[178,438,389,411]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="941">Bembecia transcaucasica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The latter taxon is here considered a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName id="F9C04D0DFFEA472AFC427AD0FEC9FE73" baseAuthorityName="LEDERER" baseAuthorityYear="1853" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Bembecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="941" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sanguinolenta">
<emphasis id="0CB4EA9CFFEA472AFC427AD0FEC9FE73" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="941">Bembecia sanguinolenta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Both 
<emphasis id="0CB4EA9CFFEA472AFE117AF6FD5DFE73" box="[392,725,418,440]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="941">
<taxonomicName id="F9C04D0DFFEA472AFE117AF6FDBDFE73" baseAuthorityName="LEDERER" baseAuthorityYear="1853" box="[392,565,418,440]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Bembecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="941" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sanguinolenta">B. sanguinolenta</taxonomicName>
transcaucasica
</emphasis>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="178757E7FFEA472AFD457AF6FCB2FE73" box="[732,826,419,440]" pageId="12" pageNumber="941">stat. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<emphasis id="0CB4EA9CFFEA472AFCF77AF6FBB6FE73" box="[878,1086,419,440]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="941">
<taxonomicName id="F9C04D0DFFEA472AFCF77AF6FC5FFE73" baseAuthorityName="STAUDINGER" baseAuthorityYear="1891" box="[878,983,419,440]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Bembecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="941" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pontica">B. pontica</taxonomicName>
turcmena
</emphasis>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="178757E7FFEA472AFF2B7A95FE85FE1E" box="[178,269,448,469]" pageId="12" pageNumber="941">stat. rev.</taxonomicNameLabel>
were sampled on the same locality. 
<emphasis id="0CB4EA9CFFEA472AFD017A94FCE6FE1D" box="[664,878,449,470]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="941">
<taxonomicName id="F9C04D0DFFEA472AFD017A94FC8CFE1D" baseAuthorityName="STAUDINGER" baseAuthorityYear="1891" box="[664,772,449,470]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Bembecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="941" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pontica">B. pontica</taxonomicName>
turcmena
</emphasis>
was only observed south of 
<collectingRegion id="FC04F86CFFEA472AFE937A8BFEBFFE38" box="[266,311,478,499]" country="Turkey" name="Van" pageId="12" pageNumber="941">Van</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
